t: no-repeat; background-position: top center; background-attachment: fixed; }\n    </style>\n    <script src="http://partner.googleadservices.com/gampad/google_service.js" type="text/javascript"> </script>\n    <script type="text/javascript"> GS_googleAddAdSenseService(&quot;ca-pub-3443918307802676&quot;); GS_googleEnableAllServices(); </script>\n    <script type="text/javascript"> GA_googleAddSlot(&quot;ca-pub-3443918307802676&quot;, &quot;Wordads_MIS_Mrec_adsafe&quot;); </script>\n    <script type="text/javascript"> GA_googleFetchAds(); </script>\n    <script type="text/javascript"> window.google_analytics_uacct = &quot;UA-52447-2&quot;; </script>\n    <script type="text/javascript">\n      var _gaq = _gaq || [];\n\t_gaq.push([\'_setAccount\', \'UA-52447-2\']);\n\t_gaq.push([\'_setDomainName\', \'none\']);\n\t_gaq.push([\'_setAllowLinker\', true]);\n\t_gaq.push([\'_initData\']);\n\t_gaq.push([\'_trackPageview\']);\n\n\t(function() {\n\t\tvar ga = document.createElement(\'script\'); ga.type = \'text/javascript\'; ga.async = true;\n\t\tga.src = (\'https:\' == document.location.protocol ? \'https://ssl\' : \'http://www\') + \'.google-analytics.com/ga.js\';\n\t\t(document.getElementsByTagName(\'head\')[0] || document.getElementsByTagName(\'body\')[0]).appendChild(ga);\n\t})();\n    </script>\n  </head>\n  <body class="archive tag tag-united-states tag-5850 custom-background primary secondary indexed single-author fixed highlander-enabled highlander-light">\n    <div id="page" class="hfeed">\n      <header role="banner" id="masthead">\n        <hgroup>\n          <h1 id="site-title">\n            <a rel="home" title="An American View of British Science Fiction" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/" shape="rect">An American View of British Science Fiction</a>\n          </h1>\n          <h2 id="site-description">A look at British science fiction and other UK genre TV from the eyes of a Midwestern yank!</h2>\n        </hgroup>\n        <a rel="home" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/" shape="rect">\n          <img alt="" height="252" width="1120" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/cropped-121793.jpg" id="header-image"></img>\n        </a>\n      </header>\n      <div id="main">\n        <section id="primary">\n          <div role="main" id="content">\n            <header class="page-header">\n              <h1 class="page-title">\n                Tag Archives:\n                <span>United States</span>\n              </h1>\n            </header>\n            <nav id="nav-above">\n              <h1 class="assistive-text section-heading">Post navigation</h1>\n            </nav>\n            <article class="post-873 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-misc-reviews category-uncategorized tag-bbc tag-britain tag-catherine-tate tag-dr-strangelove tag-peter-watkins tag-television-film tag-united-states tag-war-game has-featured-image" id="post-873">\n              <div class="entry-image">\n                <a rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to The War Game\xc2\xa0(1965)" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/2012/05/20/the-war-game-1965/" shape="rect">\n                  <img alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/title-bbc-the-war-game-1965.jpg" class="featured-image"></img>\n                </a>\n              </div>\n              <header class="entry-header">\n                <h1 class="entry-title">\n                  <a rel="bookmark" title="Permalink to The War Game\xc2\xa0(1965)" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/2012/05/20/the-war-game-1965/" shape="rect">The War Game\xc2\xa0(1965)</a>\n                </h1>\n                <div class="entry-meta">\n                  <span class="byline">\n                    Posted by\n                    <span class="author vcard">\n                      <a rel="author" title="View all posts by spdk1" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/author/spdk1/" class="url fn n" shape="rect">spdk1</a>\n                    </span>\n                  </span>\n                  <span class="sep"> \xe2\x80\x94 </span>\n                  <span class="entry-date">\n                    <time pubdate="pubdate" datetime="2012-05-20T03:25:39+00:00">May 20, 2012</time>\n                  </span>\n                </div>\n                <p class="comments-link">\n                  <a title="Comment on The War Game\xc2\xa0(1965)" href="http://anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com/2012/05/20/the-war-game-1965/#comments" shape="rect">4</a>\n                </p>\n              </header>\n              <div class="entry-content">\n                <p>\n                  There is nothing more terrifying than watching a \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93what-if?\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd film about a nuclear holocaust. If done correctly, such programs can really stir fear in one\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s heart and make anyone think about the ramifications of such an event to their lives. I particularly remember watching the American\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Television_film" title="Television film" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">TV movie</a>\n                  <em>\n                    <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Day_After" title="The Day After" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">The Day After</a>\n                  </em>\n                  some years ago, and while not acted in the best manner, it was disturbing in many ways. First of all it was filmed in my home state, using buildings and town names that I\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2m used to, and it showed what could happen after a\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_weapon" title="Nuclear weapon" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">nuclear bomb</a>\n                  falls. I can only imagine how messed up it would have been had they had done it as a faux documentary rather than a drama, it would most likely have ended up like\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BBC" title="BBC" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">BBC</a>\n                  \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s\n                  <em>\n                    <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_War_Game" title="The War Game" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">The War Game</a>\n                    \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9c\n                  </em>\n                  a far superior film, and much more scary. A film like this is only as powerful as the time we live in, and today much like the sixties, we live in fear of idiots flaunting their missiles all over the world. This short\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black-and-white" title="Black-and-white" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">black-and-white film</a>\n                  was recently added to Netflix instant streaming, so I figured that it would be interesting, little did I know it would also be amazing.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  <a href="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/the_war_game_filmposter.jpeg" shape="rect">\n                    <img height="422" width="300" alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/the_war_game_filmposter.jpeg?w=300&amp;h=422" title="The_War_Game_FilmPoster" class="aligncenter"></img>\n                  </a>\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  Produced in manner similar to a documentary-styled magazine program,\n                  <em>The War Game</em>\n                  tells the story of a nuclear crisis in the \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93near future\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd of the 1960\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s Britain. The whole mess starts when China invades\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Vietnam" title="South Vietnam" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">South Vietnam</a>\n                  , an act that America sees fitting to retaliate for with a decree of nuclear intentions. This idea angers all of the\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communist_state" title="Communist state" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Communist nations</a>\n                  leading to a small-scale nuclear war in Berlin between the two German halves and a handful of allies on either side. Eventually, it all escalates into an all-out World War with Britain getting hammered with over sixty bombs.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  <a href="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-family.jpg" shape="rect">\n                    <img height="415" width="541" alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-family.jpg?w=541&amp;h=415" title="war-game-family" class="aligncenter wp-image-876"></img>\n                  </a>\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  This film shows everything thereafter including the collapse of society, sick people, and mental traumas resulting from the bombings. What follows is a scathing look at how the director,\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Watkins" title="Peter Watkins" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Peter Watkins</a>\n                  , sees Britain\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s preparedness for such an event. All that \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93stiff upper lip\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd stoic nature from the blitz goes out the window in this documentary, and everyone turns into animals once things get bad. All\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_service" title="Civil service" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Civil service</a>\n                  agencies are lampooned as well as church elders, but this is not humorous satire, this is the stuff of nightmares.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  One of the most unnerving segments in this film was a series of black cards with white lettering read by the narrator. Throughout the film, these cards come up to show facts, news quotes, maps, and other tidbits that really help this to look like a news show. The most poignant ones were statements from officials such as government workers, press agents, and other high up big-wigs. The card that creeped me out the most concerns the manner in which the church took notice of the bombings, coming together to issue the following odd statement:\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  <a href="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-vatican-card.jpg" shape="rect">\n                    <img height="330" width="440" alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-vatican-card.jpg?w=440&amp;h=330" title="war-game-vatican-card" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-874"></img>\n                  </a>\n                </p>\n                <blockquote>\n                  <p>\xe2\x80\x9cThe church must tell the faithful that they should learn to live with, though not love, the nuclear bomb, provided that it is \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xcb\x9cclean\xe2\x80\x99 and of a good family.\xe2\x80\x9d</p>\n                </blockquote>\n                <p>And later:</p>\n                <blockquote>\n                  <p>\n                    \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93During a recent meeting of the\n                    <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecumenical_council" title="Ecumenical council" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Ecumenical Council</a>\n                    at The Vatican \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9c a bishop told the press that he was sure \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93our nuclear weapons will be used with wisdom.\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd\n                  </p>\n                </blockquote>\n                <p>\n                  With how \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93out of reality\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd the church tends to be these days, I\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2m not too convinced that something like this wouldn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t leave the lips of a spokesman at the Vatican today! I\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2m not sure whether to take stuff like this as black comedy much on the same way that\n                  <em>\n                    <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr._Strangelove" title="Dr. Strangelove" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Dr. Strangelove</a>\n                  </em>\n                  handled such things, or a hard condemnation on how stupid and/or heartless people can be. With our politicians today, I think the latter is most fitting.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  The written content found within isn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t the only thing that makes this film so dark. It\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s also filmed in a manner reminiscent of actual news footage \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9c meaning that they created staged building collapses and deaths, and filmed it all with a handheld camera to make it far more realistic than many movies of the time. This was\n                  <em>Cloverfield</em>\n                  , only forty years early. For the 1960\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s, these special effects are amazing and would honestly look great if used in a modern production. This isn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t a cardboard walls\n                  <em>Doctor Who</em>\n                  budget, this was made to look as real as it could to strike fear. I think the only effect that was sort of \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93iffy\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd was the way in which they depicted nuclear blasts. Since they didn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t have computer generated effects back then, and stock footage is tiresome, we didn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t see any mushroom clouds. Usually somebody would be outside and the screen would flash white for a moment, leading the actor to cover their eyes and scream. While not great, this effect does its job, and doesn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t look unrealistic, just uninspiring. It was like hearing the sound effects from an off-screen battle in a\n                  <em>Lord of the Rings</em>\n                  movie, some of the impact is taken away if you can\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t see it.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  <a href="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-lady.jpg" shape="rect">\n                    <img height="396" width="515" alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/war-game-lady.jpg?w=515&amp;h=396" title="war-game-lady" class="aligncenter wp-image-875"></img>\n                  </a>\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  Gritty scenes such as one featuring a group policemen being forced to employ mercy killings on people so severely injured that doctors could not help them seems so out of place for any film made in the 1960\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s. I can see why this film was immediately hated by higher-ups at the BBC, as it basically mocked authority on all levels. Also, if people used to call in to complain about things in\n                  <em>Doctor Who</em>\n                  in the 1970\xe2\x80\xb2s being \xe2\x80\x9ctoo scary\xe2\x80\x9d this would have given these same people heart attacks. I cannot stress how much this seems like a modern film in terms of tone and nature. The War Game didn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t actually get shown on any TV network until the mid-1980\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s, and I\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2m thankful it didn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t meet the same fate as other 1960\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s BBC productions \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9cwiped and junked. It was deemed too dark, it made the British infrastructure look bad, it belittled civil servants, and it stood in the face of over-zealous national pride \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9cthings that weren\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t cool forty years ago. At least now we can watch it, and enjoy it without any censorship involved.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  Another scene that really struck me, on a deja vu level, was one that was used much later for a plotline in a David Tennant era\n                  <em>Doctor Who</em>\n                  episode called\n                  <em>\n                    <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turn_Left_%28Doctor_Who%29" title="Turn Left (Doctor Who)" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Turn Left</a>\n                  </em>\n                  . In\n                  <em>The War Game</em>\n                  , threats of an imminent nuclear strike force the evacuation of millions of people to the country-side. The streets run foul with protests and uncertainty as many households were forced to take in and feed as many as eight guests for the duration of the events. People caught on camera include many that act very selfish; this includes people trying to hoard resources and even bigots. One woman interviewed remarked that she hoped her new lodgers \xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xc5\x93weren\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t colored\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xef\xbf\xbd as was the norm back in the sixties.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  <a href="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/the_war-game-blindfolded-man.png" shape="rect">\n                    <img height="312" width="440" alt="" src="http://spdk1.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/the_war-game-blindfolded-man.png?w=440&amp;h=312" title="the_war-game-blindfolded-man" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-879"></img>\n                  </a>\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  The aforementioned\n                  <em>Doctor Who</em>\n                  version of this happened in a similar manner. In\n                  <em>Turn Left</em>\n                  , the Earth fell to utter ruin when the titular character died in an alternate reality. His companion at the time, Donna as played by\n                  <a target="_blank" rel="wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catherine_Tate" title="Catherine Tate" class="zem_slink" shape="rect">Catherine Tate</a>\n                  , was forced to board with other people when London is totally destroyed in a nuclear accident. The racial sentiment is still jarring now as it was in the sixties, and it really shows that accidents and other catastrophes bring out the worst in people. I\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2m really surprised that there haven\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t been a lot of people that have picked up on this connection between the two shows accidental or intended\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x80\x9c then again this movie may be pretty obscure due to its age and its banned status.\n                </p>\n                <p>\n                  If you want to see a great disaster movie that doesn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t resort to over-the-top special effects in lieu of drama, please check this out. For a film that I assumed would be schlocky 1960\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s faire,\n                  <em>The War Game</em>\n                  was awesome. This movie is so dark, violent, pessimistic, and edgy, that one would assume that it came from the brain of a modern director. Since it was shelved so long ago, I feel that many have not seen a true speculative fiction classic. I know this kind of film is not for everyone, it\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2s sort of depressing, and makes you feel bad. But that shouldn\xc3\xa2\xe2\x82\xac\xe2\x84\xa2t stand in the way of the punch in the gut you get watching it.\n                </p>\n                <p>Here is an excerpt from the film:</p>\n                <span style="text-align:center; display: block;" class="embed-youtube">\n                  <iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/v9v-tI7xQFo?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;fs=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;wmode=transparent" height="278" width="440" type="text/html" class="youtube-player" scrolling="auto" frameborder="0"></iframe>\n                </span>\n                <div style="text-align: center; padding: 5px; padding: 5px; margin: 10px auto;" class="wpadvert">\n                  <script type="text/javascript">\n                    GA_googleAddAttr(&quot;LangId&quot;, &quot;1&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;WordAds&quot;, &quot;1&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;WordAds-MI&quot;, &quot;1&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;BlogId&quot;, &quot;13537171&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Domain&quot;, &quot;anamericanviewofbritishsciencefiction.com&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;AdSafe&quot;, &quot;1&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Autotag&quot;, &quot;movies&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Autotag&quot;, &quot;entertainment&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;misc-reviews&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;bbc&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;britain&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;catherine-tate&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;dr-strangelove&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;peter-watkins&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;television-film&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;united-states&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;Tag&quot;, &quot;war-game&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;theme_bg&quot;, &quot;ffffff&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;theme_text&quot;, &quot;111111&quot;);\nGA_googleAddAttr(&quot;theme_link&quot;, &quot;b12930&quot;);\nGA_googleAdd